Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Cerro Verde, Credicorp, Grana Y Montero

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-04T21:22:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/peru-stocks-alturas-atacocha-cerro-verde-credicorp-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index soared 6.1 percent, its largest
advance since Nov. 4, 2008, to 20,678.38. The MSCI All Peru
Capped Index increased 4.7 percent to 2,740.91.  Mining and banking stocks rose after a presidential poll
showed declining support for former military rebel Ollanta
Humala. The leader of Peru’s Nationalist Party had 39 percent
support, while Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori had 38 percent, in a
poll taken April 23-30 by Lima-based Ipsos Apoyo.  The sol strengthened 0.3 percent to 2.8195 per  U.S. dollar ,
from 2.8273 yesterday.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, soared 20 percent to 18 cents. Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc and lead
producer, jumped 13 percent to 99 centimos. Sociedad Minera
Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper
& Gold Inc., gained 6.7 percent to $41.60. Refineria la Pampilla
SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol TPF SA, climbed 15
percent to 1.88 soles.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial services
company, rose 3 percent to $97.88.  Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1
PE), the Peruvian construction company, climbed 13 percent to
5.81 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
